{
  "id": "RAW_7bbc3383",
  "title": "IDE 的终结？",
  "url": "https://addyo.substack.com/p/death-of-the-ide",
  "date": "2026-03-20 14:31:23",
  "author": "Addy Osmani",
  "siteName": "Elevate",
  "content": "<html>\n <head></head>\n <body>\n  <div dir=\"auto\" class=\"body markup\">\n   <p><strong>The </strong><em><strong>center</strong></em><strong> of developer work is moving.</strong><span> Not disappearing - moving. Away from continuous, line-by-line editing inside a single window, and </span><strong>toward supervising agents</strong><span> that can plan, rewrite files, run tests, and propose changes for review. IDEs as we know them may stop being the primary tool for software work, or heavily evolve.</span></p>\n   <p><span>Across the tools many developers including myself are already using daily - </span><a href=\"https://conductor.build/\" rel>Conductor</a><span>, </span><a href=\"https://code.claude.com/docs/en/claude-code-on-the-web\" rel>Claude Code Web</a><span>, </span><a href=\"https://github.com/copilot/agents\" rel>GitHub Copilot Agent</a><span>, </span><a href=\"http://jules.google\" rel>Jules</a><span>, </span><a href=\"https://www.vibekanban.com/\" rel>Vibe KanBan</a><span>, even cmux - the same shift keeps showing up: </span><strong>the control plane is becoming the primary surface, and the editor is becoming one of several instruments underneath it.</strong></p>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_fbfdde15-b9fc-4cf8-a399-5769c44274e7_2400x1350.jpeg\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img can-restack\"> \n      <div class=\"image2-inset can-restack\">\n       <picture><source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_fbfdde15-b9fc-4cf8-a399-5769c44274e7_2400x1350.jpeg 424w, https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_fbfdde15-b9fc-4cf8-a399-5769c44274e7_2400x1350.jpeg 848w, https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_fbfdde15-b9fc-4cf8-a399-5769c44274e7_2400x1350.jpeg 1272w, https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_fbfdde15-b9fc-4cf8-a399-5769c44274e7_2400x1350.jpeg 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\"><img src=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_fbfdde15-b9fc-4cf8-a399-5769c44274e7_2400x1350.jpeg\" width=\"1456\" height=\"819\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/fbfdde15-b9fc-4cf8-a399-5769c44274e7_2400x1350.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:819,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:466191,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://addyo.substack.com/i/191542117?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ffbfdde15-b9fc-4cf8-a399-5769c44274e7_2400x1350.jpeg&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" alt srcset=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_fbfdde15-b9fc-4cf8-a399-5769c44274e7_2400x1350.jpeg 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/328ef8e9-3927-44dd-368b-294c70d98d00/public 848w, https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_fbfdde15-b9fc-4cf8-a399-5769c44274e7_2400x1350.jpeg 1272w, https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_fbfdde15-b9fc-4cf8-a399-5769c44274e7_2400x1350.jpeg 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" fetchpriority=\"high\" class=\"sizing-normal\"></picture>\n       <div class=\"image-link-expand\">\n        <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\">\n         <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container restack-image\">\n          <svg role=\"img\" style=\"height:20px;width:20px\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" fill=\"none\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke=\"var(--color-fg-primary)\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\">\n           <g>\n            <title></title><path d=\"M2.53001 7.81595C3.49179 4.73911 6.43281 2.5 9.91173 2.5C13.1684 2.5 15.9537 4.46214 17.0852 7.23684L17.6179 8.67647M17.6179 8.67647L18.5002 4.26471M17.6179 8.67647L13.6473 6.91176M17.4995 12.1841C16.5378 15.2609 13.5967 17.5 10.1178 17.5C6.86118 17.5 4.07589 15.5379 2.94432 12.7632L2.41165 11.3235M2.41165 11.3235L1.5293 15.7353M2.41165 11.3235L6.38224 13.0882\"></path>\n           </g>\n          </svg>\n         </button>\n         <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container view-image\">\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2\">\n           <polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line>\n          </svg>\n         </button>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div> \n     </a>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p><span>Cursor just shipped </span><a href=\"https://cursor.com/glass\" rel>Glass</a><span> - a new interface explicitly built to make “working with agents clear, intuitive, and in your control” where agent management is the primary experience and the traditional editor is something you reach for when you need to go deeper. The </span><a href=\"https://x.com/F2aldi/status/2034801927041818823\" rel>reaction</a><span> from developers was immediate: </span></p>\n   <blockquote>\n    <p><em>Now Cursor feels more like an Agent Orchestrator than an IDE. Managing agents in parallel is easier</em></p>\n   </blockquote>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_48500cf2-98ed-4280-8ae9-25e3ae8d0669_1920x1080.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img can-restack\"> \n      <div class=\"image2-inset can-restack\">\n       <picture><source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_48500cf2-98ed-4280-8ae9-25e3ae8d0669_1920x1080.png 424w, https://image.jido.dev/20260320223547_48500cf2-98ed-4280-8ae9-25e3ae8d0669_1920x1080.png 848w, https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_48500cf2-98ed-4280-8ae9-25e3ae8d0669_1920x1080.png 1272w, https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_48500cf2-98ed-4280-8ae9-25e3ae8d0669_1920x1080.png 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\"><img src=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_48500cf2-98ed-4280-8ae9-25e3ae8d0669_1920x1080.png\" width=\"1456\" height=\"819\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/48500cf2-98ed-4280-8ae9-25e3ae8d0669_1920x1080.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:819,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:619387,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://addyo.substack.com/i/191542117?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F48500cf2-98ed-4280-8ae9-25e3ae8d0669_1920x1080.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" alt srcset=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_48500cf2-98ed-4280-8ae9-25e3ae8d0669_1920x1080.png 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/737e3d1d-823b-49d8-23d7-cabef7031d00/public 848w, https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_48500cf2-98ed-4280-8ae9-25e3ae8d0669_1920x1080.png 1272w, https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_48500cf2-98ed-4280-8ae9-25e3ae8d0669_1920x1080.png 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" class=\"sizing-normal\"></picture>\n       <div class=\"image-link-expand\">\n        <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\">\n         <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container restack-image\">\n          <svg role=\"img\" style=\"height:20px;width:20px\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" fill=\"none\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke=\"var(--color-fg-primary)\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\">\n           <g>\n            <title></title><path d=\"M2.53001 7.81595C3.49179 4.73911 6.43281 2.5 9.91173 2.5C13.1684 2.5 15.9537 4.46214 17.0852 7.23684L17.6179 8.67647M17.6179 8.67647L18.5002 4.26471M17.6179 8.67647L13.6473 6.91176M17.4995 12.1841C16.5378 15.2609 13.5967 17.5 10.1178 17.5C6.86118 17.5 4.07589 15.5379 2.94432 12.7632L2.41165 11.3235M2.41165 11.3235L1.5293 15.7353M2.41165 11.3235L6.38224 13.0882\"></path>\n           </g>\n          </svg>\n         </button>\n         <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container view-image\">\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2\">\n           <polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line>\n          </svg>\n         </button>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div> \n     </a>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p><span>But Glass is one data point in a much larger pattern. Terminal UIs like </span><a href=\"https://cmux.com/\" rel>cmux</a><span> highlight how the surfaces we’re used to are evolving to better manage agent workflows.</span></p>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_936597fd-b43d-4b9e-8e0c-f6ae8aaa9929_3840x2224.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img can-restack\"> \n      <div class=\"image2-inset can-restack\">\n       <picture><source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_936597fd-b43d-4b9e-8e0c-f6ae8aaa9929_3840x2224.png 424w, https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_936597fd-b43d-4b9e-8e0c-f6ae8aaa9929_3840x2224.png 848w, https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_936597fd-b43d-4b9e-8e0c-f6ae8aaa9929_3840x2224.png 1272w, https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_936597fd-b43d-4b9e-8e0c-f6ae8aaa9929_3840x2224.png 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\"><img src=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_936597fd-b43d-4b9e-8e0c-f6ae8aaa9929_3840x2224.png\" width=\"1456\" height=\"843\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/936597fd-b43d-4b9e-8e0c-f6ae8aaa9929_3840x2224.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:843,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;cmux terminal app screenshot&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" alt=\"cmux terminal app screenshot\" title=\"cmux terminal app screenshot\" srcset=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_936597fd-b43d-4b9e-8e0c-f6ae8aaa9929_3840x2224.png 424w, https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_936597fd-b43d-4b9e-8e0c-f6ae8aaa9929_3840x2224.png 848w, https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_936597fd-b43d-4b9e-8e0c-f6ae8aaa9929_3840x2224.png 1272w, https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_936597fd-b43d-4b9e-8e0c-f6ae8aaa9929_3840x2224.png 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" class=\"sizing-normal\"></picture>\n       <div class=\"image-link-expand\">\n        <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\">\n         <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container restack-image\">\n          <svg role=\"img\" style=\"height:20px;width:20px\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" fill=\"none\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke=\"var(--color-fg-primary)\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\">\n           <g>\n            <title></title><path d=\"M2.53001 7.81595C3.49179 4.73911 6.43281 2.5 9.91173 2.5C13.1684 2.5 15.9537 4.46214 17.0852 7.23684L17.6179 8.67647M17.6179 8.67647L18.5002 4.26471M17.6179 8.67647L13.6473 6.91176M17.4995 12.1841C16.5378 15.2609 13.5967 17.5 10.1178 17.5C6.86118 17.5 4.07589 15.5379 2.94432 12.7632L2.41165 11.3235M2.41165 11.3235L1.5293 15.7353M2.41165 11.3235L6.38224 13.0882\"></path>\n           </g>\n          </svg>\n         </button>\n         <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container view-image\">\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2\">\n           <polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line>\n          </svg>\n         </button>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div> \n     </a>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <h2 class=\"header-anchor-post\">From editing files to steering workstreams\n    <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent\">\n     <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA\">\n      <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" aria-label=\"Link\" data-href=\"https://addyo.substack.com/i/191542117/from-editing-files-to-steering-workstreams\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o\">\n       <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-link\">\n        <path d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\"></path><path d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\"></path>\n       </svg>\n      </button>\n     </div>\n    </div></h2>\n   <p><span>Historically, IDEs optimized for a tight inner loop: open files → edit → build → debug → repeat. </span><strong>The “death” argument is that this loop is no longer the dominant unit of productivity once agents can execute most of it autonomously.</strong></p>\n   <p><span>The new loop looks like this: </span><strong>specify intent → delegate → observe → review diffs → merge</strong><span>. What makes it different from “autocomplete with a chat window” is tool-using autonomy combined with interfaces designed to make that autonomy governable.</span></p>\n   <p>You can see this playing out across tools already in heavy use. Claude Code Web (or Desktop) and Codex let developers hand off well-defined tasks to agents running in isolated cloud environments, with progress visible in a browser - no terminal, no local setup required.</p>\n   <p>GitHub Copilot’s Agents plan and implements multi-file changes independently, creates branches, runs tests, and surfaces a PR for review; the developer’s primary job becomes reviewing the outcome and iterating, not directing each step.</p>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260320150316_8f9eef48-c593-4a33-a05c-cd2602ef85ff_3018x1664.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img can-restack\"> \n      <div class=\"image2-inset can-restack\">\n       <picture><source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_8f9eef48-c593-4a33-a05c-cd2602ef85ff_3018x1664.png 424w, https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_8f9eef48-c593-4a33-a05c-cd2602ef85ff_3018x1664.png 848w, https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_8f9eef48-c593-4a33-a05c-cd2602ef85ff_3018x1664.png 1272w, https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_8f9eef48-c593-4a33-a05c-cd2602ef85ff_3018x1664.png 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\"><img src=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_8f9eef48-c593-4a33-a05c-cd2602ef85ff_3018x1664.png\" width=\"549\" height=\"302.779532967033\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/8f9eef48-c593-4a33-a05c-cd2602ef85ff_3018x1664.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:803,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:549,&quot;bytes&quot;:549881,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://addyo.substack.com/i/191542117?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F8f9eef48-c593-4a33-a05c-cd2602ef85ff_3018x1664.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" alt srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/91d1e32d-9855-4a8e-31cd-c8481d6b7c00/public 424w, https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_8f9eef48-c593-4a33-a05c-cd2602ef85ff_3018x1664.png 848w, https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_8f9eef48-c593-4a33-a05c-cd2602ef85ff_3018x1664.png 1272w, https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_8f9eef48-c593-4a33-a05c-cd2602ef85ff_3018x1664.png 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\"></picture>\n       <div class=\"image-link-expand\">\n        <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\">\n         <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container restack-image\">\n          <svg role=\"img\" style=\"height:20px;width:20px\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" fill=\"none\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke=\"var(--color-fg-primary)\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\">\n           <g>\n            <title></title><path d=\"M2.53001 7.81595C3.49179 4.73911 6.43281 2.5 9.91173 2.5C13.1684 2.5 15.9537 4.46214 17.0852 7.23684L17.6179 8.67647M17.6179 8.67647L18.5002 4.26471M17.6179 8.67647L13.6473 6.91176M17.4995 12.1841C16.5378 15.2609 13.5967 17.5 10.1178 17.5C6.86118 17.5 4.07589 15.5379 2.94432 12.7632L2.41165 11.3235M2.41165 11.3235L1.5293 15.7353M2.41165 11.3235L6.38224 13.0882\"></path>\n           </g>\n          </svg>\n         </button>\n         <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container view-image\">\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2\">\n           <polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line>\n          </svg>\n         </button>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div> \n     </a>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p>Conductor takes a different approach: a desktop app for running multiple Claude Code agents simultaneously in isolated workspaces, with live progress monitoring across all of them. And Google’s Jules handles asynchronous background tasks - you assign work, it runs, you review the result when it’s done.</p>\n   <p><span>What these tools share is a mental model: </span><strong>the agent is the unit of work, not the file</strong><span>. The interface worth optimizing is the one that helps you direct, monitor, and review agents - not the one that helps you type faster.</span></p>\n   <h2 class=\"header-anchor-post\">The orchestration layer taking shape\n    <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent\">\n     <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA\">\n      <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" aria-label=\"Link\" data-href=\"https://addyo.substack.com/i/191542117/the-orchestration-layer-taking-shape\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o\">\n       <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-link\">\n        <path d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\"></path><path d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\"></path>\n       </svg>\n      </button>\n     </div>\n    </div></h2>\n   <p>The displacement story becomes persuasive only when you look at the specific interface patterns converging across tools.</p>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260320150316_13e9d9a9-4541-4381-b6b8-14d07e95a2c2_2500x1774.avif\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img can-restack\"> \n      <div class=\"image2-inset can-restack\">\n       <picture><source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_13e9d9a9-4541-4381-b6b8-14d07e95a2c2_2500x1774.avif 424w, https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_13e9d9a9-4541-4381-b6b8-14d07e95a2c2_2500x1774.avif 848w, https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_13e9d9a9-4541-4381-b6b8-14d07e95a2c2_2500x1774.avif 1272w, https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_13e9d9a9-4541-4381-b6b8-14d07e95a2c2_2500x1774.avif 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\"><img src=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_13e9d9a9-4541-4381-b6b8-14d07e95a2c2_2500x1774.avif\" width=\"562\" height=\"398.72664835164835\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/13e9d9a9-4541-4381-b6b8-14d07e95a2c2_2500x1774.avif&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1033,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:562,&quot;bytes&quot;:136737,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/avif&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://addyo.substack.com/i/191542117?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F13e9d9a9-4541-4381-b6b8-14d07e95a2c2_2500x1774.avif&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" alt srcset=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_13e9d9a9-4541-4381-b6b8-14d07e95a2c2_2500x1774.avif 424w, https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_13e9d9a9-4541-4381-b6b8-14d07e95a2c2_2500x1774.avif 848w, https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_13e9d9a9-4541-4381-b6b8-14d07e95a2c2_2500x1774.avif 1272w, https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_13e9d9a9-4541-4381-b6b8-14d07e95a2c2_2500x1774.avif 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\"></picture>\n       <div class=\"image-link-expand\">\n        <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\">\n         <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container restack-image\">\n          <svg role=\"img\" style=\"height:20px;width:20px\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" fill=\"none\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke=\"var(--color-fg-primary)\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\">\n           <g>\n            <title></title><path d=\"M2.53001 7.81595C3.49179 4.73911 6.43281 2.5 9.91173 2.5C13.1684 2.5 15.9537 4.46214 17.0852 7.23684L17.6179 8.67647M17.6179 8.67647L18.5002 4.26471M17.6179 8.67647L13.6473 6.91176M17.4995 12.1841C16.5378 15.2609 13.5967 17.5 10.1178 17.5C6.86118 17.5 4.07589 15.5379 2.94432 12.7632L2.41165 11.3235M2.41165 11.3235L1.5293 15.7353M2.41165 11.3235L6.38224 13.0882\"></path>\n           </g>\n          </svg>\n         </button>\n         <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container view-image\">\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2\">\n           <polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line>\n          </svg>\n         </button>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div> \n     </a>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p><strong>Work isolation as a primitive.</strong><span> Parallel agents need to not step on each other. Virtually every serious tool in this space has landed on git worktrees (or similar) as the answer. Conductor maps each agent session to its own isolated workspace. Vibe Kanban (shown above) does the same for its kanban-driven agent workflow. The pattern is near ubiquitous because the problem is real: without isolation, parallel agents produce chaos.</span></p>\n   <p><strong>Planning and task state as the primary UI.</strong><span> Tools like Vibe Kanban have replaced “tabs and files” with “tasks and states” as the top-level mental model. You create task cards (a landing page, a backend service, an email integration), assign each to an agent and a model, and manage the whole effort like a lightweight project board - except the “team” is running autonomously. This is a project management surface that happens to have agents doing the implementation.</span></p>\n   <p><strong>Background agents and async-first design.</strong><span> Some of the most interesting tools in this space don’t even try to keep you in the loop during execution. Cursor, Copilot and Antigravity support background agents that run without requiring your presence - you define intent, step away, and review when they’re done. Jules works similarly: assign a task, come back to a diff. The implicit promise is that your attention is too valuable to spend watching a progress bar. That’s a significant departure from the IDE’s real-time, synchronous feedback loop.</span></p>\n   <p><strong>Attention management for parallel agents.</strong><span> When many agents run concurrently, the real bottleneck becomes knowing which one needs you </span><em>right now</em><span>. This is why tools like Conductor surface live progress across sessions and cmux introduced notification rings and unread badges for terminal panes. “Agent needs attention” is becoming a first-class event in the developer environment - something to route and triage, not just notice.</span></p>\n   <p><strong>Agents embedded into the software lifecycle.</strong><span> GitHub’s Copilot coding agent is asynchronous, secured by a control layer, and powered by GitHub Actions - attached to how code actually ships (issues → PRs → CI → merge), not just how it gets written. </span></p>\n   <p>None of these tools claim IDEs are obsolete - many still interoperate with them. But the repeated patterns (parallel workspaces, diff-first review, task state, background execution, lifecycle integration) are precisely what “death of the IDE” proponents mean when they talk about a center-of-gravity shift.</p>\n   <h2 class=\"header-anchor-post\">Why developers still reach for an IDE\n    <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent\">\n     <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA\">\n      <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" aria-label=\"Link\" data-href=\"https://addyo.substack.com/i/191542117/why-developers-still-reach-for-an-ide\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o\">\n       <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-link\">\n        <path d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\"></path><path d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\"></path>\n       </svg>\n      </button>\n     </div>\n    </div></h2>\n   <p><strong>The best critique of “the IDE is dead” is that the IDE </strong><em><strong>still</strong></em><strong> compresses several genuinely hard problems into a high-fidelity feedback loop</strong><span>: precise navigation, local reasoning, interactive debugging, and the ability to </span><em>understand</em><span> a system by directly manipulating it.</span></p>\n   <p>Even the most ambitious orchestration tools keep a manual-edit escape hatch. For example, reviewing diffs in-thread, commenting on changes, and then opening the result in your editor for manual adjustments. That’s an acknowledgment that human intervention is part of the intended workflow.</p>\n   <p>Agent tooling itself highlights where the limits still are. Multi-file refactorings in large repositories remain among the toughest challenges for software engineering agents. These are exactly the situations where interactive code navigation and human judgment still matter most - where you need to hold a mental model of the system that the agent can’t fully reconstruct from context alone.</p>\n   <p><span>The failure mode that keeps developers anchored to IDE-level inspection is agents being </span><em>almost</em><span> right. When something is 90% correct and subtly broken, the cost of finding the issue often exceeds what it would have taken to write it yourself. For high-stakes changes, the IDE remains the best instrument for that kind of deep, precise inspection.</span></p>\n   <h2 class=\"header-anchor-post\">The new costs: review fatigue and governance overhead\n    <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent\">\n     <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA\">\n      <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" aria-label=\"Link\" data-href=\"https://addyo.substack.com/i/191542117/the-new-costs-review-fatigue-and-governance-overhead\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o\">\n       <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-link\">\n        <path d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\"></path><path d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\"></path>\n       </svg>\n      </button>\n     </div>\n    </div></h2>\n   <p>If development becomes “run many agents in parallel” the workflow inherits problems that look less like text editing and more like distributed systems management - observability, permissions, isolation, and governance.</p>\n   <p>Agent workflows invert the labor. Instead of writing, you’re reviewing. That sounds like an improvement until you’re staring at twelve diffs from twelve parallel agents at the end of the day. Review fatigue is real, and it’s one of the reasons the most thoughtful tools in this space focus on attention routing, structured plans, and review-first gates rather than pushing for full autonomy by default.</p>\n   <p><span>The security surface also expands as agents gain access to more tools, repos, and external systems. As agents can browse the web, query databases, write to filesystems, and trigger deploys, what they’re </span><em>allowed</em><span> to do becomes as important as what they’re </span><em>capable</em><span> of doing.</span></p>\n   <p>On observability and control, IDE-integrated agent modes are already pushing toward explicit tool logs and approval gates. The governance question isn’t optional once agents act asynchronously and touch CI pipelines.</p>\n   <h2 class=\"header-anchor-post\">What survives: the IDE, the control plane, or both\n    <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent\">\n     <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA\">\n      <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" aria-label=\"Link\" data-href=\"https://addyo.substack.com/i/191542117/what-survives-the-ide-the-control-plane-or-both\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o\">\n       <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-link\">\n        <path d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\"></path><path d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\"></path>\n       </svg>\n      </button>\n     </div>\n    </div></h2>\n   <p><span>A clear reading of the landscape is that “death of the IDE” is directionally right about the </span><em>center of gravity</em><span>, but wrong as a literal forecast.</span></p>\n   <p><span>The strongest version of the claim is this: </span><strong>the IDE stops being the primary workspace and becomes one of several subordinate instruments</strong><span> - used for targeted inspection, debugging, and final edits - while planning, orchestration, review, and agent management move into dashboards, issue trackers, observability terminals, and cloud control planes. </span></p>\n   <p><span>The “bigger IDE” framing is equally well-supported. The new “IDE” is a system that provides multi-agent orchestration, isolated workspaces, permissions and audit logs, diff-first review, reliable tool connectivity, and attention routing. </span><strong>The file editor is still there. It’s just no longer the front door.</strong></p>\n   <p><span>The IDE isn’t dying. It’s being </span><em>de-centered</em><span>. The work is moving outward - into orchestration surfaces where humans define intent, delegate to parallel agent runtimes, and spend more time supervising, reviewing, and governing than typing. </span></p>\n   <p><strong>The IDE remains critical for correctness, comprehension, and the hard problems agents still struggle with. But its no longer the only place where programming happens - and for a growing number, it’s no longer the first place they go.</strong></p>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/3bde2dfc-ca6f-4a1d-f7e9-3fd86ac19a00/public\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img can-restack\"> \n      <div class=\"image2-inset can-restack\">\n       <picture><source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_e0294ae8-2a3c-4dbc-93b5-5c7d6283a9ee_1376x768.jpeg 424w, https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_e0294ae8-2a3c-4dbc-93b5-5c7d6283a9ee_1376x768.jpeg 848w, https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_e0294ae8-2a3c-4dbc-93b5-5c7d6283a9ee_1376x768.jpeg 1272w, https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_e0294ae8-2a3c-4dbc-93b5-5c7d6283a9ee_1376x768.jpeg 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\"><img src=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_e0294ae8-2a3c-4dbc-93b5-5c7d6283a9ee_1376x768.jpeg\" width=\"1376\" height=\"768\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/e0294ae8-2a3c-4dbc-93b5-5c7d6283a9ee_1376x768.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:768,&quot;width&quot;:1376,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:31526,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://addyo.substack.com/i/191542117?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe0294ae8-2a3c-4dbc-93b5-5c7d6283a9ee_1376x768.jpeg&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" alt srcset=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_e0294ae8-2a3c-4dbc-93b5-5c7d6283a9ee_1376x768.jpeg 424w, https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_e0294ae8-2a3c-4dbc-93b5-5c7d6283a9ee_1376x768.jpeg 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/f5132f0f-9b18-4797-dbbc-962ada80fa00/public 1272w, https://image.jido.dev/20260320150315_e0294ae8-2a3c-4dbc-93b5-5c7d6283a9ee_1376x768.jpeg 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\"></picture>\n       <div class=\"image-link-expand\">\n        <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\">\n         <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container restack-image\">\n          <svg role=\"img\" style=\"height:20px;width:20px\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" fill=\"none\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke=\"var(--color-fg-primary)\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\">\n           <g>\n            <title></title><path d=\"M2.53001 7.81595C3.49179 4.73911 6.43281 2.5 9.91173 2.5C13.1684 2.5 15.9537 4.46214 17.0852 7.23684L17.6179 8.67647M17.6179 8.67647L18.5002 4.26471M17.6179 8.67647L13.6473 6.91176M17.4995 12.1841C16.5378 15.2609 13.5967 17.5 10.1178 17.5C6.86118 17.5 4.07589 15.5379 2.94432 12.7632L2.41165 11.3235M2.41165 11.3235L1.5293 15.7353M2.41165 11.3235L6.38224 13.0882\"></path>\n           </g>\n          </svg>\n         </button>\n         <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container view-image\">\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2\">\n           <polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line>\n          </svg>\n         </button>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div> \n     </a>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p></p>\n  </div>\n </body>\n</html>",
  "aiSummary": "本文探讨了软件开发从 IDE 中逐行手动编辑向“控制平面”模型的转变，后者专注于编排和监督自主 AI 智能体。",
  "oneSentenceSummary": "本文探讨了软件开发从 IDE 中逐行手动编辑向“控制平面”模型的转变，后者专注于编排和监督自主 AI 智能体。",
  "summary": "Addy Osmani 分析了开发者工具的演进格局，认为 IDE 正在被“去中心化”而非被取代。随着智能体获得自主规划、执行和测试代码的能力，主要的开发者工作流正从同步的“编辑-构建-调试”循环转向异步的“指定-委托-审查”模式。文章重点介绍了 Cursor、GitHub Copilot 和 Claude Code 等工具的新兴模式，包括通过 git worktree 进行工作隔离、基于任务的 UI 和并行智能体管理。虽然 IDE 仍对深入理解系统和修复细微的 AI 错误至关重要，但编程的“入口”正在转向优先考虑意图和治理而非原始打字速度的编排界面。",
  "mainPoints": [
    {
      "point": "开发的重心正从编辑转向编排。",
      "explanation": "现代工具正从逐行手动编辑转向“控制平面”，开发者可以在其中监督能够独立规划和执行多文件更改的智能体。"
    },
    {
      "point": "“工作单元”正从单个文件转向自主智能体。",
      "explanation": "新界面优先管理智能体状态和任务进度，而非传统的文件标签页，将智能体视为实现功能的主要实体。"
    },
    {
      "point": "工作隔离和并行执行正成为核心工作流原语。",
      "explanation": "为了防止混乱，成熟的智能体工具利用 git worktree 或隔离的云环境，让多个智能体同时处理不同任务而互不干扰。"
    },
    {
      "point": "IDE 仍然是高保真推理和调试的重要“逃生舱”。",
      "explanation": "当智能体产出“90% 正确”但存在细微问题的代码时，IDE 的精确导航和交互式调试工具对于人工干预和系统理解是必要的。"
    },
    {
      "point": "并行智能体的兴起带来了审查疲劳和治理等新成本。",
      "explanation": "随着开发者转变为监督者，瓶颈从编写代码转向审查大量并行 diff 和管理智能体权限的认知负担。"
    }
  ],
  "keyQuotes": [
    "开发者工作的重心正在转移。不是消失——而是转移。从单个窗口中连续的逐行编辑，转移到监督智能体。",
    "智能体是工作单元，而非文件。值得优化的界面是帮助你引导、监控和审查智能体的界面。",
    "IDE 并未消亡。它正在被去中心化。工作正在向外转移——转移到编排界面，在那里人类定义意图并花更多时间进行监督。",
    "当某物 90% 正确但存在细微问题时，找到问题的成本往往超过自己编写的成本。",
    "IDE 不再是主要工作空间，而是变成用于针对性检查、调试和最终编辑的多个辅助工具之一。"
  ],
